The paper deals with the weight distributions of linear convolutional codes, which are typically studied in the information theory (cs.IT) and coding theory (cs.DS) communities. The use of generating functions and the MacWilliams identity also suggests a connection to the field of symbolic computation and algebraic manipulation (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the performance estimation of codes, which is relevant to the computer communications (cs.CC) and networking (cs.NI) communities.
